  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the analgesic efficacy of three different types of
      video/audio distraction in normal volunteers subjected to carefully controlled and
      non-injurious thermal pain delivered to the skin of the lower back, simulating discomfort of
      a lumbar puncture. Two of the distraction techniques include immersive virtual reality (VR).
      The most efficacious distraction technique will be used in a subsequent clinical study in
      cancer patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
